** `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n\n- **strict:** true\n- **target:** ES2022\n- **module:** Node16\n- **moduleResolution:** Node16\n- **outDir:** `./dist`\n- **rootDir:** `./src`\n- **declaration:** true\n- **esModuleInterop:** true\n- **skipLibCheck:** true\n- **include:** `src/**/*`\n\n---\n\n### 4. `vitest.config.ts`\n\n**File:** `/workspace/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Type System -- `/workspace/src/core/types.ts`\n\nThis file defines 6 interfaces that form the entire type foundation:\n\n**`SiteConfig`** -- Site-wide configuration:\n- `title: string` -- site title\n- `baseUrl: string` -- e.g. `https://example.com`\n- `outputDir: string` -- build output directory\n- `contentDir: string` -- source content directory\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- A single content document:\n- `slug: string` -- URL-friendly identifier\n- `title: string` -- document title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key-value metadata\n- `date?: string` -- optional publication date\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag list\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name override\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- The shared state passed through the build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- the site config\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- the content files being processed\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path -> rendered content (e.g. `\"post-1.html\"` -> HTML string)\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path -> binary data\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (inter-plugin communication)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- The three lifecycle hooks a plugin can implement:\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content transformation\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- transforms each file individually\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after template rendering\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The plugin interface:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this depends on (used for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the lifecycle hooks\n\n**`Template`** -- A rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template name (e.g. `\"default\"`, `\"list\"`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- render function\n\n---\n\n### 6. Build Engine -- `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class is the heart of the SSG. It has:\n\n**Private state:**\n- `plugins: Plugin[]` -- registered plugins\n- `templates: Map<string, Template>` -- registered templates\n\n**Constructor:** Takes a `SiteConfig`.\n\n**`registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void`** -- Pushes a plugin onto the array.\n\n**`registerTemplate(template: Template): void`** -- Stores a template by name.\n\n**`resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]`** -- Topological sort using DFS:\n- Builds a `pluginMap` (name -> Plugin)\n- Uses `visited` (fully processed) and `visiting` (currently in DFS stack) sets\n- Throws `\"Circular dependency detected: ${name}\"` if a cycle is found\n- Throws `\"Missing dependency: ${name} requires ${dep}\"` if a dependency is not registered\n- Returns plugins in dependency-first order\n\n**`async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`** -- The main build pipeline:\n1. Creates a `BuildContext` with shallow-copied files, empty output/assets/data Maps\n2. Resolves plugin execution order via `resolvePluginOrder()`\n3. **Phase 1 -- beforeBuild hooks:** Runs each plugin's `beforeBuild` in dependency order\n4. **Phase 2 -- transformContent hooks:** For each plugin (in order), transforms ALL files through that plugin's `transformContent` hook. Each plugin sees the output of the previous plugin.\n5. **Phase 3 -- Template rendering:** For each file, looks up the template by `file.template` (defaulting to `\"default\"`). Renders with data including title, slug, date, tags, all metadata, siteTitle, and baseUrl. Output key is `\"${file.slug}.html\"`. If no matching template, outputs raw `file.content`.\n6. **Phase 4 -- afterBuild hooks:** Runs each plugin's `afterBuild` in dependency order\n7. Returns the `BuildContext`\n\n**`getPlugins(): Plugin[]`** -- Returns a copy of the plugins array.\n\n**`getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>`** -- Returns a copy of the templates map.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Templates -- `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- Returns a Template named `\"default\"` that renders:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{title} | {siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>{title}</h1>\n    {optional <time>{date}</time>}\n    <div class=\"content\">{content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**`createListTemplate()`** -- Returns a Template named `\"list\"` that renders:\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>{title} | {siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>{title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">{content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Barrel Export -- `/workspace/src/core/index.ts`\n\nRe-exports everything:\n- `BuildEngine` from `./engine.js`\n- `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate` from `./templates.js`\n- All types: `BuildContext`, `ContentFile`, `Plugin`, `PluginHooks`, `SiteConfig`, `Template` from `./types.js`\n\n---\n\n### 9. Core Tests -- `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`\n\n15 tests covering the `BuildEngine`:\n\n| # | Test | What It Verifies |\n|---|------|-----------------|\n| 1 | registers plugins | `getPlugins()` returns registered plugin |\n| 2 | registers templates | `getTemplates()` has the registered template |\n| 3 | builds with default template | Renders HTML with DOCTYPE, title, content, siteTitle |\n| 4 | builds with list template | Renders list HTML with `<div class=\"list\">` |\n| 5 | outputs raw content when no matching template | Falls back to raw `file.content` |\n| 6 | calls plugin beforeBuild hook | Verifies beforeBuild is invoked |\n| 7 | calls plugin transformContent hook | Verifies content is transformed (uppercased) |\n| 8 | calls plugin afterBuild hook | Verifies afterBuild is invoked |\n| 9 | executes plugins in dependency order | Plugin \"b\" depends on \"a\" -> order is [a, b] |\n| 10 | throws on circular dependency | a->b, b->a throws \"Circular dependency\" |\n| 11 | throws on missing dependency | a->missing throws \"Missing dependency\" |\n| 12 | applies multiple plugins transformContent in order | \"first\" then \"second\" appended sequentially |\n| 13 | provides shared data store | Plugin sets `ctx.data` in beforeBuild, verified after |\n| 14 | retains file metadata through build | metadata, date, tags survive the pipeline |\n| 15 | produces empty output for empty file list | No files -> no output, empty files array |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Plugin Test Files -- `/workspace/tests/plugins/`\n\nEach test file imports from `../../src/plugins/<name>.js` expecting a `create<Name>Plugin()` factory function that returns a `Plugin` object. All plugins are to be implemented in `src/plugins/`.\n\n#### 10a. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import:** `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n**Hook used:** `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| converts basic markdown to HTML | `# Hello` -> `<h1>`, `**bold**` -> `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| handles footnotes with [^1] syntax | `text[^1]` -> `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| renders footnote section at bottom | `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` |\n| converts :::note container | `:::note\\n...\\n:::` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` |\n| converts :::warning container | `:::warning\\n...\\n:::` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">` |\n| converts :::tip container | `:::tip\\n...\\n:::` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">` |\n| preserves existing HTML | Already-HTML content kept intact |\n| handles empty content | No crash on empty string |\n\n#### 10b. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import:** `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n**Hook used:** `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `src=\"./image.png\"` -> `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` -> `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `https://cdn.example.com/...` untouched |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` -> `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | Content unchanged |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | All 3 assets in manifest |\n| asset manifest includes all discovered assets | Across multiple `transformContent` calls |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `/assets/image.png` left as-is, no manifest entry |\n\n#### 10c. `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import:** `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n**Hook used:** `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| adds language class to code blocks | `class=\"language-javascript\"` -> `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute to pre tags | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Both get `data-language` |\n| handles code block with no language | `<pre><code>` unchanged, no \"highlighted\" class |\n| adds highlighted class | `highlighted` class present |\n| preserves code block content | Code text preserved exactly |\n| handles empty code blocks | Still gets `data-language` and `highlighted` |\n| does not modify inline code | `<code>` not inside `<pre>` is untouched |\n\n#### 10d. `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import:** `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n**Hooks used:** `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` with correct counts |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` containing post titles |\n| handles files with no tags | tagMap.size === 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | All 3 tags in map |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Both posts appear on the tag page |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `taxonomy-tags` key exists |\n| handles empty file list | No errors, tagMap.size === 0 |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `'JavaScript'` and `'JAVASCRIPT'` both become `'javascript'` |\n\n#### 10e. `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import:** `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\n**Hook used:** `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies:** markdown-ext, taxonomy\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown | `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | `<category>javascript</category>` from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` |\n| feed includes channel title from config | `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New -> Mid -> Old ordering |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| feed link uses baseUrl from config | `<link>https://example.com</link>` and per-item links |\n\n#### 10f. `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import:** `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\n**Hook used:** `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies:** markdown-ext, syntax-highlight\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates search-index.json | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, plain text | HTML stripped, fields present |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `const x = 1;` present in plain text |\n| handles empty file list | Returns `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | Parses without error, is array with correct length |\n| index entries include tags if present | `tags: ['js', 'web']` in entry |\n\n#### 10g. `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import:** `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\n**Hook used:** `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies:** taxonomy, rss-feed\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | All `.html` pages with full baseUrl |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | `tags/javascript.html` in sitemap |\n| includes feed.xml URL | `feed.xml` in sitemap |\n| URLs use baseUrl from config | Full URLs like `https://example.com/about.html` |\n| sitemap is valid XML structure | `<?xml`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | No `/tags/` in output |\n\n#### 10h. `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import:** `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\n**Hook used:** `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies:** asset-pipeline, search-index\n\nLocal interface defined in test:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `config.port` is a number |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | reads `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')`, assetPaths includes files, routes have `handler: 'asset'` |\n| config includes search index path | `/search-index.json` if present in output |\n| config includes content routes | `.html` entries get `handler: 'static'` routes |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully | `assetPaths` defaults to `[]` |\n\n---\n\n### 11. Plugin Dependency DAG (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  - markdown-ext\n  - asset-pipeline\n  - syntax-highlight\n  - taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  - rss-feed        -> depends on: markdown-ext, taxonomy\n  - search-index    -> depends on: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight\n\nWave 3 (depend on Wave 2):\n  - sitemap         -> depends on: taxonomy, rss-feed\n  - dev-server      -> depends on: asset-pipeline, search-index\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. Summary of What Needs to Be Built\n\nThe `src/plugins/` directory is currently empty (just a `.gitkeep`). Eight plugin files need to be created, each exporting a factory function:\n\n| File | Factory Function | Hooks Used | Dependencies |\n|------|-----------------|------------|-------------|\n| `src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts` | `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` | `transformContent` | none |\n| `src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts` | `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` | `transformContent` | none |\n| `src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts` | `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` | `transformContent` | none |\n| `src/plugins/taxonomy.ts` | `createTaxonomyPlugin()` | `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild` | none |\n| `src/plugins/rss-feed.ts` | `createRssFeedPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | markdown-ext, taxonomy |\n| `src/plugins/search-index.ts` | `createSearchIndexPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | markdown-ext, syntax-highlight |\n| `src/plugins/sitemap.ts` | `createSitemapPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | taxonomy, rss-feed |\n| `src/plugins/dev-server.ts` | `createDevServerPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | asset-pipeline, search-index |\n\nThe total test count is: 15 existing core tests + 60 new plugin tests (8+8+8+8+7+7+7+7) = 75 tests total that must pass."}],"totalDurationMs":103130,"totalTokens":36915,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13040,"cache_read_input_tokens":18374,"output_tokens":5500,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13040,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
